If dispose is called immediately after initialize your binding should be able to shutdown without side effects.
In this case it is possible for dispose to be called before you have initialized the touchWandWebSockets field.
To prevent this from happening you need use a boolean isRunning field along with synchronization to make sure that access to the isRunning and touchWandWebSockets field is atomic.
You could synchronize on a new lock object, but for this fix it is less messy to just synchronize on the this object instead.
